data.description:
Welcome to this truly remarkable property in Teller County that boats a 3,000sq foot home with guest cabin on 73 +/- acres and bordering national forest off of the famed Gold Camp Rd.

 Located at the end of the road and gated for privacy, there is ample room to spread out in this 5 bedroom / 2 bath home complete with wood burning stove downstairs, propane stove upstairs as well as radiant heat.   The open floor plan allows for easy entertaining while your guests take in the dramatic views looking south west towards pring reservoir. The kitchen is equipped with high end appliances such a a large Sub-Zero refrigerator, Wolf gas stove and stainless range hood. 

 Below the main level is a walkout basement which has 2 bedrooms, utility room as well as a quaint live edge bar. Power on this property is supplemented by the large 4 panel solar system so that if the electricity ever goes out, you are covered.  Extensive road and dirt work has been done on this property to make is both usable and easy to access.

Multiple buildings are utilized here to include a 60 x 60 garage/ metal shop with concrete floor, wooden barn with hay loft, loafing shed as well as a 400 sq ft unfinished guest cabin with separate access. 

This property offers access via atv trail to thousands of acres of public land located in GMU 59 which has over the counter opportunities for big game hunting. 

Often times you will find elk and deer grazing on the grass located on this fantastic property

Call to schedule an exclusive showing of this remarkable property.
